"{\"uid\": \"thenation.com-article-society-paris-olympics-counter-protests-opening\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Forgot Your Password?\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 23, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"New toThe Nation?Subscribe  Print subscriber?Activateyour online access  \\\"The Olympic Games are profoundly disrupting the lives of French people,\\\" the protesters wrote in a joint statement.\", \"from\": 25, \"to\": 214, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 156, \"end\": 169, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French people\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The question then arises: Who benefits from the Games?\\\"\", \"from\": 214, \"to\": 270, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A protester at the Counter-Opening of the Olympics event in Paris on July 25, 2024.\", \"from\": 272, \"to\": 355, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 332, \"end\": 337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.359075455196344e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the night before the opening of the 2024 Paris Olympics, several thousand activists mobilized at Place de la R\\u00e9publique for speeches, a DJ set, and interviews with swarms of international journalists.\", \"from\": 357, \"to\": 560, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 457, \"end\": 479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_R\\u00e9publique\", \"score\": 0.9919463876317131, \"rank\": 0.007170795306387261, \"text\": \"Place de la R\\u00e9publique\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_R\\u00e9publique\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_R\\u00e9publique\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dubbed the \\\"Counter-Opening Ceremony of the Olympics,\\\" the event featured more than 80 grassroots organizations that signed onto a statement titled \\\"des Jeux, mais pour qui?\\\"\", \"from\": 561, \"to\": 735, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(\\\"Games, but for whom?\\\")\", \"from\": 736, \"to\": 760, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Among the organizations were trade unions, environmental groups, civil-liberties organizations, and residents of Saint Denis, an area in the north of the city deeply and negatively affected by the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 761, \"to\": 970, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 880, \"end\": 885, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maurice_Denis\", \"score\": 0.999708120676368, \"rank\": 0.0002155965141402442, \"text\": \"Denis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maurice_Denis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maurice_Denis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The activist collectiveLe Revers de la M\\u00e9daille(the Other Side of the Medal) coordinated the raucous gathering.\", \"from\": 971, \"to\": 1082, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ahead of the mobilization, Le Revers de la M\\u00e9daille issueda joint statementon behalf of the wider coalition in the major French newspaperLib\\u00e9rationtitled, \\\"Inclusive, Popular, Carbon-neutral Olympics?\", \"from\": 1084, \"to\": 1284, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1114, \"end\": 1120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revers\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Revers\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revers\"}, {\"begin\": 1205, \"end\": 1211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9995125357511017, \"rank\": 0.0002803177388804468, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No Way!\\\"\", \"from\": 1285, \"to\": 1293, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In their scathing missive, they slammed Olympic organizers and elected officials for a slew of false pledges.\", \"from\": 1294, \"to\": 1403, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We see that the Olympic Games are profoundly disrupting the lives of French people, without the promised legacy being delivered,\\\" the group wrote.\", \"from\": 1404, \"to\": 1551, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1474, \"end\": 1487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French people\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The question then arises: who benefits from the Games?\\\"\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1608, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Antoine de Clerck, of Le Revers de la M\\u00e9daille, explained to us that the purpose of the \\\"Counter-Opening Ceremony\\\" was \\\"to raise public awareness of what's happening, but also to have a little bit of a party together.\\\"\", \"from\": 1610, \"to\": 1828, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1621, \"end\": 1627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Alexander_Clerck\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Clerck\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Alexander_Clerck\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Alexander_Clerck\"}, {\"begin\": 1635, \"end\": 1641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revers\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Revers\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Because of the intensified displacement the Games have brought about, he said, \\\"it has been a really difficult last days and weeks.\\\"\", \"from\": 1829, \"to\": 1961, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Running like a lightning bolt through the protest was solidarity with Palestine.\", \"from\": 1963, \"to\": 2043, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2033, \"end\": 2042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\", \"score\": 0.9999998963840024, \"rank\": 1.0361577322834013e-07, \"text\": \"Palestine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Flags, keffiyehs, and speakers showcased an iron link between the Palestinian cause and the counter-Olympics struggle.\", \"from\": 2044, \"to\": 2162, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2110, \"end\": 2121, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"score\": 0.9999131369315853, \"rank\": 8.686976307452525e-05, \"text\": \"Palestinian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The presence of Israeli athletes at the Games-and the way it normalizes the state of Israel-is seen as a particularly brutal example of \\\"sportswashing.\\\"\", \"from\": 2163, \"to\": 2315, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2179, \"end\": 2186, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 0.9999998644889366, \"rank\": 6.784839293292478e-08, \"text\": \"Israeli\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many of the speakers made this link between the Olympics and the need for Palestinian solidarity.\", \"from\": 2316, \"to\": 2413, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2390, \"end\": 2401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"score\": 0.9999131369315853, \"rank\": 8.686976307452525e-05, \"text\": \"Palestinian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Genocide is not a spectator sport\\\" has become an ubiquitous slogan among protesters.\", \"from\": 2414, \"to\": 2499, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even rally speakers, like a group of African migrants whose squat was destroyed as part of the Olympic \\\"social cleansing,\\\" connected their displacement with Gaza.\", \"from\": 2500, \"to\": 2662, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2657, \"end\": 2661, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"score\": 0.999998499284846, \"rank\": 1.5007173273804785e-06, \"text\": \"Gaza\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The rally also showcased the internationalism of what has become an \\\"anti-Olympic movement\\\" throughout the world.\", \"from\": 2664, \"to\": 2777, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When Natsuko Sasaki from the anti-Olympics groupSaccage 2024took the stage, she unveiled \\\"the anti-Olympics torch,\\\" a toilet plunger festooned with cloth ribbons bearing anti-Games slogans.\", \"from\": 2778, \"to\": 2967, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2783, \"end\": 2790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Natsuko_(album)\", \"score\": 0.5031580251945039, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Natsuko\", \"types\": [\"Q482994\", \"Q386724\", \"Q2188189\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Natsuko_(album)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Natsuko_(album)\"}, {\"begin\": 2791, \"end\": 2797, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Terufumi_Sasaki\", \"score\": 0.7550140119640087, \"rank\": 0.32134168268985447, \"text\": \"Sasaki\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Terufumi_Sasaki\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Terufumi_Sasaki\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This torch was born 14 years ago by activists in Canada who opposed the Vancouver 2010 Winter Olympics.\", \"from\": 2968, \"to\": 3071, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3017, \"end\": 3023, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.182181889366349e-15, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the time, longtime anti-poverty activist Jean Swanson bought ribbons from the dollar store and decorated the plunger with them.\", \"from\": 3072, \"to\": 3202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3116, \"end\": 3128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_Swanson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jean Swanson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_Swanson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_Swanson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Little did she know that the torch would make its way around the world.\", \"from\": 3203, \"to\": 3274, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Vancouver activists passed the torch to London-based anti-Games organizer Julian Cheyne, who brought it to protests against the 2012 London Olympics.\", \"from\": 3276, \"to\": 3425, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He then gave it to a New Jersey-based group of Circassian activists protesting the 2014 Sochi Olympics.\", \"from\": 3426, \"to\": 3529, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3473, \"end\": 3483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Circassians\", \"score\": 0.9890858020003614, \"rank\": 0.011034632157210799, \"text\": \"Circassian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Circassians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Circassians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The alternative torch eventually made its way to Rio for the 2016 Summer Olympics and Pyeongchang for the 2018 Winter Games before arriving in Tokyo, where it was prominently featured at the first-ever transnational anti-Olympics summit in 2019, just ahead of the Covid-plagued 2020 Games.\", \"from\": 3530, \"to\": 3819, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3579, \"end\": 3582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 0.9997870948538545, \"rank\": 0.000212021198372501, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}, {\"begin\": 3616, \"end\": 3627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pyeongchang_County\", \"score\": 0.9998812281254563, \"rank\": 0.00011878598275260889, \"text\": \"Pyeongchang\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pyeongchang_County\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pyeongchang_County\"}, {\"begin\": 3673, \"end\": 3678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.810944099895199e-13, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A spirit of democracy pervaded the proceedings, as members of this French resistance spoke to reporters and passers-by.\", \"from\": 3821, \"to\": 3940, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3888, \"end\": 3905, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Resistance\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.089109848825295e-15, \"text\": \"French resistance\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Resistance\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Resistance\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This spirit is not being matched by the International Olympic Committee, which is renting out the H\\u00f4tel du Collectionneur for a whopping 22 million euros.\", \"from\": 3941, \"to\": 4095, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3981, \"end\": 4012, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to German journalist and Olympics watchdog Jens Weinreich, the IOC havebarredreporters from entering the premises, a first in decades.\", \"from\": 4096, \"to\": 4240, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4109, \"end\": 4115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9988279659303562, \"rank\": 0.001170427918037667, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC has become a bastion of authoritarianism under current president Thomas Bach-exactly what the French haverejectedat the ballot box.\", \"from\": 4241, \"to\": 4380, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4245, \"end\": 4248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.177351840846212e-41, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 4314, \"end\": 4320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"score\": 0.9999999968649718, \"rank\": 3.135393566548724e-09, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\"}, {\"begin\": 4343, \"end\": 4349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9995125357511017, \"rank\": 0.0002803177388804468, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the workers at the hotel are not letting the IOC live in a bubble.\", \"from\": 4382, \"to\": 4452, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4431, \"end\": 4434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.177351840846212e-41, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They coordinated a walkout to demand salary hikes on the day before the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 4453, \"to\": 4542, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Their union, the Union D\\u00e9partementale CGT Paris,tweeted, \\\"We can not wait for the workers of the world to discover our French way of striking.\\\"\", \"from\": 4543, \"to\": 4686, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4581, \"end\": 4584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_Confederation_of_Labour_of_the_Argentines\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.230226916793082e-27, \"text\": \"CGT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_Confederation_of_Labour_of_the_Argentines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_Confederation_of_Labour_of_the_Argentines\"}, {\"begin\": 4585, \"end\": 4590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.359075455196344e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4662, \"end\": 4668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9995125357511017, \"rank\": 0.0002803177388804468, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let the Games begin?\", \"from\": 4688, \"to\": 4708, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They have already begun.\", \"from\": 4709, \"to\": 4733, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even before February 28, the reasons for Donald Trump's imploding approval rating were abundantly clear: untrammeled corruption and personal enrichment to the tune of billions of dollars during an affordability crisis, a foreign policy guided only by his own derelict sense of morality, and the deployment of a murderous campaign of occupation, detention, and deportation on American streets.\", \"from\": 4735, \"to\": 5127, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4776, \"end\": 4788, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.8870426761150883e-12, \"text\": \"Donald Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 5110, \"end\": 5118, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1060492582385574e-15, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now an undeclared, unauthorized, unpopular, and unconstitutional war of aggression against Iran has spread like wildfire through the region and into Europe.\", \"from\": 5129, \"to\": 5285, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5220, \"end\": 5224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"score\": 0.9999674925029104, \"rank\": 2.5036013847113627e-05, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A new \\\"forever war\\\"-with an ever-increasing likelihood of American troops on the ground-may very well be upon us.\", \"from\": 5286, \"to\": 5399, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5344, \"end\": 5352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1060492582385574e-15, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As we have seen over and over, this administration uses lies, misdirection, and attempts to flood the zone to justify its abuses of power at home and abroad.\", \"from\": 5401, \"to\": 5558, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just as Trump, Marco Rubio, and Pete Hegseth offer erratic and contradictory rationales for the attacks on Iran, the administration is also spreading the lie that the upcoming midterm elections are under threat from noncitizens on voter rolls.\", \"from\": 5559, \"to\": 5802, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5567, \"end\": 5572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999999998681233, \"rank\": 1.3161552362018785e-10, \"text\": \"Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 5574, \"end\": 5585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marco_Rubio\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.744866333015841e-34, \"text\": \"Marco Rubio\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marco_Rubio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marco_Rubio\"}, {\"begin\": 5591, \"end\": 5603, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pete_Hegseth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pete Hegseth\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pete_Hegseth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pete_Hegseth\"}, {\"begin\": 5666, \"end\": 5670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"score\": 0.9999674925029104, \"rank\": 2.5036013847113627e-05, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When these lies go unchecked, they become the basis for further authoritarian encroachment and war.\", \"from\": 5803, \"to\": 5902, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In these dark times, independent journalism is uniquely able to uncover the falsehoods that threaten our republic-and civilians around the world-and shine a bright light on the truth.\", \"from\": 5904, \"to\": 6087, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Nation's experienced team of writers, editors, and fact-checkers understands the scale of what we are up against and the urgency with which we have to act.\", \"from\": 6089, \"to\": 6248, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's why we are publishing critical reporting and analysis of the war on Iran, ICE violence at home, new forms of voter suppression emerging in the courts, and much more.\", \"from\": 6249, \"to\": 6421, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6324, \"end\": 6328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"score\": 0.9999674925029104, \"rank\": 2.5036013847113627e-05, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But this journalism is possible only with your support.\", \"from\": 6423, \"to\": 6478, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This March,The Nationneeds to raise $50,000 to ensure that we have the resources for reporting and analysis that sets the record straight and empowers people of conscience to organize.Will you donate today?\", \"from\": 6480, \"to\": 6686, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dave Zirin is the sports editor atThe Nation.\", \"from\": 6688, \"to\": 6733, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6688, \"end\": 6698, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dave_Zirin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dave Zirin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dave_Zirin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dave_Zirin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is the author of 11 books on the politics of sports.\", \"from\": 6734, \"to\": 6789, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He is also the coproducer and writer of the new documentaryBehind the Shield: The Power and Politics of the NFL.\", \"from\": 6790, \"to\": 6902, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6898, \"end\": 6901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\", \"score\": 0.9998886541864688, \"rank\": 7.913952424074768e-05, \"text\": \"NFL\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jules Boykoff is a professor of political science at Pacific University in Oregon and the author of six books on the Olympic Games, most recentlyWhat Are the Olympics For?\", \"from\": 6904, \"to\": 7075, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6904, \"end\": 6917, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jules_Boykoff\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jules Boykoff\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jules_Boykoff\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jules_Boykoff\"}, {\"begin\": 6957, \"end\": 6975, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pacific_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pacific University\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pacific_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pacific_University\"}, {\"begin\": 6979, \"end\": 6985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oregon\", \"score\": 0.9999963649490967, \"rank\": 3.635055900183232e-06, \"text\": \"Oregon\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oregon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oregon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Gaza, we wa